{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"035c1087-d441-4d80-8e3a-c579456d6d7a","content":"Since MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 already includes Microsoft.Testing.Platform support, the migration is straightforward. Here's what to change in your project file:\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's the key change — `MSTest.Sdk` 3.4+ defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is **not** set to `true`.\n\n### Other things to be aware of:\n\n1. **Test runner command changes** — Instead of `dotnet test`, you can now also run tests directly via the built executable. `dotnet test` still works but routes through the new platform.\n\n2. **CLI differences** — Some VSTest CLI options (e.g., `--filter`) change syntax. The new equivalent uses `--filter` with a slightly different expression format. Run your test project with `--help` to see available options.\n\n3. **`.runsettings` compatibility** — Most `.runsettings` options still work, but review any VSTest-specific adapter settings you may have.\n\n4. **Remove any explicit VSTest adapter packages** — If you reference `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` or VSTest adapter packages manually, remove them; `MSTest.Sdk` handles everything.\n\n### Minimal diff:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nAfter the change, run `dotnet test` to verify all tests still pass.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a62bb607-680c-4db4-8f91-6e5e50936ebe","outputTokens":463,"requestId":"4C15:3F94EE:DA3F35:10E8099:6A0129EE"},"id":"1215d2dc-d9f3-4838-b3ca-c47a0eb2a63a","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:59:36.908Z","parentId":"de6b71e1-2375-497a-ab3b-bd534aa8eedd"}
